How to setup UniFi Video on Debian
1. Install the latest version of Debian with only SSH server selected

Update the system if needed
2. apt-get update
3. apt-get upgrade

Install sudo and add user to sudo
4. apt-get install sudo
5. usermod -aG sudo (username)

Install unattended-upgrades
6. apt-get install unattended-upgrades

Install ca-certificates
7. apt-get install ca-certificates

Install prerequisites
8. apt-get install mongodb mongodb-server openjdk-8-jre-headless jsvc

Install UniFi Video
Go to the temp directory
9. cd /tmp/
Download the installation UniFi Video deb file
10. wget (deb direct url)
Install the UniFi Video deb file
11. dpkg -i (deb file)
